                <h1>When Was Treasure Island Written? Discover Its History</h1>
                <p>Treasure Island was written by Robert Louis Stevenson and published in 1883. This classic adventure novel follows young Jim Hawkins as he embarks on a thrilling quest for buried pirate treasure. The story, featuring memorable characters like Long John Silver, has captivated readers for generations and remains a staple of children's literature.</p>
